tus within Beckett studies, emphasising a return to primary sources amid letters, drafts, and other documents. Major Beckett critics such as Steven Connor, David Lloyd, Andrew Gibson, John Pilling, Jean-Michel Rabaté, and Mark Nixon, as well as emerging researchers, present the latest critical thinking in 9 key areas: Art & Aesthetics; Fictions; European Context; Irish Context; Film, Radio & Television; Language/Writing; Philosophies; Theatre & Performance; Global Beckett. Edited by eminent Beckett scholar S. E. Gontarski, the Companion draws on the most vital, ground-breaking research to outline the nature of Beckett studies for the next generation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aArts, Moderny20th century. 0aArts, Moderny21st century. 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh1 aAckerley, C. J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCascetta, Annamaria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChevallier, Geneviève, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aConnor, Steven, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeldman, Matthew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFifield, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrost, Everett C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGibson, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGontarski, S. E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerren, Graley, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHouppermans, Sjef, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKennedy, Seán, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/voc